(158, 1, '2020-03-13 09:29:47', '2020-03-13 09:29:47', '<header class=\"entry-header\">\r\n<h1 class=\"entry-title\">LIJIANG, CHINA´S BIGGEST TOURIST TRAP</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n<div class=\"entry-content\" data-content-ads-inserted=\"true\"><span id=\"dpsp-post-content-markup\" data-image-pin-it=\"false\"></span>Lijiang, in Yunnan Province, is the closest thing you will get to a real wonderland. Well, that’s how it would seem without the crowds of tourists. Along with the Badaling Great Wall section, it is one of the most notorious tourist traps in China.\r\n\r\nThe Old Town of Lijiang (the new town is like any other Chinese city) is a well-preserved old city of ethnic minorities. It is closed for cars and motorbikes; the local Naxi Minority Culture on display.\r\n\r\nEven though it has become an extremely popular place for tourists, Lijiang is a great place to kick back for a few days. My first visit to Lijiang was in 2008. Although tourists were plentiful back then, it is nothing like what it became in 2016. Once a place of the only family-owned restaurants; Old Town now features a Starbucks and a Burger King. Prices in restaurants and bars are heavily influenced by a large number of visitors and can be quite expensive.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to accommodation, however, the Lijiang area does offer some of the cheapest International Hostels in China. You are required to pay a ticket price of  80 RMB even to enter Old Town. You can still get in for free by skipping the main entrance and opting for a side street.\r\n\r\nBut don’t let the tourist trap scare you away from visiting. It´s definitely a worthwhile destination if you are travelling through the Yunnan Province in Southwestern China. Your itinerary should include a visit to the Wangu Pavillion. Its located on a hill overlooking the Old Town and offers great views.\r\n<div id=\"attachment_8753\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\" data-slot-rendered-dynamic=\"true\"><img id=\"MTU4MjgyOTI4Ni44MDQ5\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8753 lazyloaded\" src=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4663.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" srcset=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4663.jpg 1500w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4663-768x458.jpg 768w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4663-600x358.jpg 600w\" alt=\"The Wangu Temple that over looks lijiang\" width=\"1500\" height=\"895\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8753\" data-pin-description=\"The Wangu Temple that over looks lijiang\" data-pin-title=\"Lijiang, China´s Biggest Tourist Trap\" />\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-8753\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The Wangu Temple that overlooks Lijiang.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_8755\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img id=\"MTU4MjgyOTE0OS44MDYz\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8755 lazyloaded\" src=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4634.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" srcset=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4634.jpg 1500w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4634-768x377.jpg 768w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4634-600x294.jpg 600w\" alt=\"Lijiang old town as seen from Wangu Temple\" width=\"1500\" height=\"736\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8755\" data-pin-description=\"Lijiang old town as seen from Wangu Temple\" data-pin-title=\"Lijiang, China´s Biggest Tourist Trap\" />\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-8755\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Lijiang old town as seen from Wangu Temple</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"mv-video-target mv-video__featured mv-video__optimized mediavine-video__target-div\" data-playlist-id=\"upnext\" data-autoplay=\"true\" data-automobile=\"true\" data-muted=\"true\" data-sticky=\"true\" data-autoinsert=\"true\" data-disable-jsonld=\"true\">\r\n<div id=\"8fa3ecfb-78a8-4c22-bea1-aa365a8af497_container\">\r\n<div id=\"8fa3ecfb-78a8-4c22-bea1-aa365a8af497_app-container\">\r\n<div class=\"mediavine-video__app\">\r\n<div class=\"mediavine-video__player-wrapper mediavine-video__sticky-wrapper\">\r\n<div class=\"mediavine-video__sticky-placement\">\r\n<div class=\"mediavine-video__sticky-container mediavine-video__bottom mediavine-video__right mediavine-video__dark\">\r\n<div class=\"mediavine-video__sticky-video\">\r\n<div id=\"8fa3ecfb-78a8-4c22-bea1-aa365a8af497-player\" class=\"mediavine-video__player\">\r\n<div id=\"video-8fa3ecfb-78a8-4c22-bea1-aa365a8af497\" class=\"video-js vjs-default-skin vjs-big-play-centered vjs-paused video-8fa3ecfb-78a8-4c22-bea1-aa365a8af497-dimensions vjs-fluid vjs-controls-enabled vjs-workinghover vjs-v7 vjs-user-active\" lang=\"en-us\" tabindex=\"-1\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Video Player\">\r\n<div class=\"vjs-text-track-display\" aria-live=\"off\" aria-atomic=\"true\"></div>\r\n<img id=\"MTU4MjgyOTY5OS44MDc3\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8764 lazyloaded\" src=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/source/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Bilde-1101.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" srcset=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/source/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Bilde-1101.jpg 1500w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Bilde-1101-768x512.jpg 768w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Bilde-1101-600x400.jpg 600w\" alt=\"Mu Palace, The palace where the Mu Clan of the Naxi people ruled for over 400 years\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8764\" data-pin-description=\"Mu Palace, The palace where the Mu Clan of the Naxi people ruled for over 400 years\" data-pin-title=\"Lijiang, China´s Biggest Tourist Trap\" />\r\n<div id=\"attachment_8764\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\" data-slot-rendered-dynamic=\"true\">\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-8764\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Mu Palace, The palace where the Mu Clan of the Naxi people ruled for over 400 years.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nBesides the obvious attractions, I found it most enjoyable to explore the labyrinth of back alleys.  If you happen to get lost, there are streams that run all over the city. Just follow a stream North, and you will end up at the water wheel near the main entrance.\r\n<div class=\"mks_col\" data-slot-rendered-dynamic=\"true\">\r\n<div class=\"mks_one_half\">\r\n<div id=\"attachment_8799\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-8799 lazyloaded\" src=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMG_3651-e1479913476745.jpg\" alt=\"just follow the streams\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1500\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8799\" data-pin-description=\"just follow the streams\" data-pin-title=\"Lijiang, China´s Biggest Tourist Trap\" />\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-8799\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Just follow the streams</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"mks_one_half\">\r\n<div id=\"attachment_8801\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-8801 lazyloaded\" src=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMG_3635-e1479913432244.jpg\" alt=\"There´s gold fishes swimming around the strams\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1500\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8801\" data-pin-description=\"There´s gold fishes swimming around the strams\" data-pin-title=\"Lijiang, China´s Biggest Tourist Trap\" />\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-8801\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Goldfish swim throughout the streams.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_8800\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img id=\"MTU4MjgyOTA5MS44MDk=\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8800 lazyloaded\" src=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/source/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMG_3639.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" srcset=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/source/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMG_3639.jpg 1500w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMG_3639-768x512.jpg 768w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMG_3639-600x400.jpg 600w\" alt=\"Romantic back allyes\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8800\" data-pin-description=\"Romantic back allyes\" data-pin-title=\"Lijiang, China´s Biggest Tourist Trap\" />\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-8800\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Romantic back allies.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_8771\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\" data-slot-rendered-dynamic=\"true\"><img id=\"MTU4MjgyOTU1NS44MTAy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8771 lazyloaded\" src=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lijiang.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" srcset=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lijiang.jpg 1500w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lijiang-768x510.jpg 768w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lijiang-600x399.jpg 600w\" alt=\"If you follow the streams will you allways end up back at the main waterwheel in old town, here late in the eveening when its lighted up.\" width=\"1500\" height=\"997\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8771\" data-pin-description=\"If you follow the streams will you allways end up back at the main waterwheel in old town, here late in the eveening when its lighted up.\" data-pin-title=\"Lijiang, China´s Biggest Tourist Trap\" />\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-8771\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">If you follow the streams will you always end up back at the main waterwheel in Old Town, here late in the evening when it’s lighted up?</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJust outside of Old Town you can find the <em>Mao Zedong</em> statue. It is easily accessible by foot.\r\n<div id=\"attachment_8756\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\" data-slot-rendered-dynamic=\"true\"><img id=\"MTU4MjgyODgxMC44MTE1\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8756 lazyloaded\" src=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4626.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" srcset=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4626.jpg 1500w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/re