static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lijiang.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" srcset=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lijiang.jpg 1500w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lijiang-768x510.jpg 768w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lijiang-600x399.jpg 600w\" alt=\"If you follow the streams will you allways end up back at the main waterwheel in old town, here late in the eveening when its lighted up.\" width=\"1500\" height=\"997\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8771\" data-pin-description=\"If you follow the streams will you allways end up back at the main waterwheel in old town, here late in the eveening when its lighted up.\" data-pin-title=\"Lijiang, China´s Biggest Tourist Trap\" />\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-8771\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">If you follow the streams will you always end up back at the main waterwheel in Old Town, here late in the evening when it’s lighted up?</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJust outside of Old Town you can find the <em>Mao Zedong</em> statue. It is easily accessible by foot.\r\n<div id=\"attachment_8756\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\" data-slot-rendered-dynamic=\"true\"><img id=\"MTU4MjgyODgxMC44MTE1\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8756 lazyloaded\" src=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4626.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" srcset=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4626.jpg 1500w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4626-768x456.jpg 768w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4626-600x356.jpg 600w\" alt=\"The Mao Zedong Statue in Lijiang\" width=\"1500\" height=\"891\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8756\" data-pin-description=\"The Mao Zedong Statue in Lijiang\" data-pin-title=\"Lijiang, China´s Biggest Tourist Trap\" />\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-8756\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The Mao Zedong Statue in Lijiang</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nAlso, be sure to check out Jade Spring Park (Black Dragon Pool Park). Its located about 1km from the main water wheel.\r\n<div id=\"attachment_8770\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\" data-slot-rendered-dynamic=\"true\"><img id=\"MTU4MjgyODk4My44MTI3\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8770 lazyloaded\" src=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/source/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4580-1.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" srcset=\"https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/source/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4580-1.jpg 1500w, https://d3eh3svpl1busq.cloudfront.net/PWOBkKVcZtPlHVzElMnvyrQsTCZwhJZy/assets/static/optimized/rev-1573951/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/IMGP4580-1-768x509.jpg 768w\" alt=\"Jade Spring Park (Black Dragon Pool Park) with theJade Dragon Snow Mountain in the back\" width=\"1500\" height=\"994\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8770\" data-pin-description=\"Jade Spring Park (Black Dragon Pool Park) with theJade Dragon Snow Mountain in the back\" data-pin-title=\"Lijiang, China´s Biggest Tourist Trap\" />\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-8770\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Jade Spring Park (Black Dragon Pool Park) with the Jade Dragon Snow Mountain in the back.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_13914\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" data-slot-rendered-dynamic=\"true\">\r\n<p id=\"caption-attachment-13914\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Lijiang, in Yunnan Province, is the closest thing you will get to a true wonderland. Well, that’s how it would seem without the crowds of tourists. Along with the Badaling Great Wall section, it is one of the most notorious tourist traps in China.3</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Old Town of Lijiang', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '158-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-13 09:27:27', '2020-03-13 09:27:27', '', 158, 'http://localhost:8888/mai/2020/03/13/158-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
